#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs0.5"
msgid "2. Omasavādasikkhāpada"
msgstr "Monks’ Confession 2: the training rule on abusive speech"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.5"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.2.1"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.2.1.1"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.171"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa29"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.1"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Sāvatthī in the Jeta Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s Monastery."

#. VAR: bhaṇḍantā → bhaṇḍentā (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.2"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū pesalehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ bhaṇḍantā pesale bhikkhū omasanti—"
msgstr "At that time the monks from the group of six were arguing with and abusing good monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.3"
msgid "jātiyāpi, nāmenapi, gottenapi, kammenapi, sippenapi, ābādhenapi, liṅgenapi, kilesenapi, āpattiyāpi; hīnenapi akkosena khuṃsenti vambhenti."
msgstr "They reviled and insulted them about their caste, name, family, work, craft, illnesses, physical traits, defilements, and offenses, and by calling them names."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.4"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.5"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.6"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū pesalehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ bhaṇḍantā pesale bhikkhū omasissanti—"
msgstr "“How can the monks from the group of six argue with and abuse good monks?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.7"
msgid "jātiyāpi, nāmenapi, gottenapi, kammenapi, sippenapi, ābādhenapi, liṅgenapi, kilesenapi, āpattiyāpi; hīnenapi akkosena khuṃsessanti vambhessantī”ti."
msgstr "How can they revile and insult them about these things?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa30"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.8"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing those monks in many ways, they told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.9"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, pesalehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ bhaṇḍantā pesale bhikkhū omasatha—jātiyāpi … pe … hīnenapi akkosena khuṃsetha vambhethā”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you are acting like this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.10"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.11"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.12"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, pesalehi bhikkhūhi saddhiṃ bhaṇḍantā pesale bhikkhū omasissatha—"
msgstr "“… Foolish men, how can you argue with and abuse good monks?"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.172"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.13"
msgid "jātiyāpi … pe … hīnenapi akkosena khuṃsessatha vambhessatha."
msgstr "How can you revile and insult them about their caste, name, family, work, craft, illnesses, physical traits, defilements, and offenses, and by calling them names?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.14"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.15"
msgid "vigarahitvā … pe …"
msgstr "… and after rebuking them …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.1.16"
msgid "dhammiṃ kathaṃ katvā bhikkhū āmantesi—"
msgstr "he gave a teaching and addressed the monks:"

#. </p><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Jataka"

#. </h5><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><div class="jataka"><p><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.2.1.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa31"></a> 
#. VAR: takkasilāyaṃ → takkasīlāyaṃ (mr)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.1"
msgid "“Bhūtapubbaṃ, bhikkhave, takkasilāyaṃ aññatarassa brāhmaṇassa nandivisālo nāma balībaddo ahosi."
msgstr "“Once upon a time, monks, there was a brahmin in Takkasilā who had an ox called Nandivisāla."

#. VAR: balībaddo → balivaddo (bj) | balibaddo (s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.2"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, nandivisālo balībaddo taṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca—‘"
msgstr "On one occasion the ox said to the brahmin,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.3"
msgid "gaccha tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, seṭṭhinā saddhiṃ sahassena abbhutaṃ karohi—"
msgstr "‘Go, brahmin, and make the following bet worth one thousand coins with a prominent merchant:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.4"
msgid "mayhaṃ balībaddo sakaṭasataṃ atibaddhaṃ pavaṭṭessatī’ti."
msgstr "“My ox will pull one hundred carts tied together.”’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.5"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, so brāhmaṇo seṭṭhinā saddhiṃ sahassena abbhutaṃ akāsi—"
msgstr "And that brahmin did just that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.6"
msgid "mayhaṃ balībaddo sakaṭasataṃ atibaddhaṃ pavaṭṭessatīti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.7"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, so brāhmaṇo sakaṭasataṃ atibandhitvā nandivisālaṃ balībaddaṃ yuñjitvā etadavoca—"
msgstr "Then, after tying one hundred carts together and yoking Nandivisāla to them, he said,"

#. VAR: gaccha, kūṭa → añcha kūṭa (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.8"
msgid "‘gaccha, kūṭa, vahassu, kūṭā’ti."
msgstr "‘Go, you fraud; pull, you liar.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.9"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, nandivisālo balībaddo tattheva aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr "But Nandivisāla just stood right there."

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.10"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, so brāhmaṇo sahassena parājito pajjhāyi."
msgstr "Then that brahmin became depressed because he had lost one thousand coins."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.11"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, nandivisālo balībaddo taṃ brāhmaṇaṃ etadavoca—‘"
msgstr "And Nandivisāla said to him,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.12"
msgid "kissa tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, pajjhāyasī’ti?"
msgstr "‘Why are you depressed?’"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.13"
msgid "‘Tathā hi panāhaṃ, bho, tayā sahassena parājito’ti."
msgstr "‘Because I lost one thousand coins because of you.’"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.14"
msgid "‘Kissa pana maṃ tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, akūṭaṃ kūṭavādena pāpesi?"
msgstr "‘But why did you disgrace me by calling me a fraud when I’m not?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.15"
msgid "Gaccha tvaṃ, brāhmaṇa, seṭṭhinā saddhiṃ dvīhi sahassehi abbhutaṃ karohi—"
msgstr "Now go, brahmin, and make the same bet worth two thousand coins with that merchant."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.16"
msgid "“mayhaṃ balībaddo sakaṭasataṃ atibaddhaṃ pavaṭṭessatī”’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.17"
msgid "‘Mā ca maṃ akūṭaṃ kūṭavādena pāpesī’ti."
msgstr "But don’t disgrace me by calling me a fraud.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.18"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, so brāhmaṇo seṭṭhinā saddhiṃ dvīhi sahassehi abbhutaṃ akāsi—‘"
msgstr "Once again that brahmin did just that."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.19"
msgid "mayhaṃ balībaddo sakaṭasataṃ atibaddhaṃ pavaṭṭessatī’ti."
msgstr ""

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.173"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.20"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, so brāhmaṇo sakaṭasataṃ atibandhitvā nandivisālaṃ balībaddaṃ yuñjitvā etadavoca—‘"
msgstr "Then, after tying one hundred carts together and yoking Nandivisāla to them, he said,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.21"
msgid "gaccha, bhadra, vahassu, bhadrā’ti."
msgstr "‘Go, good ox; pull, good ox.’"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.22"
msgid "Atha kho, bhikkhave, nandivisālo balībaddo sakaṭasataṃ atibaddhaṃ pavaṭṭesi."
msgstr "And Nandivisāla pulled those one hundred carts."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa32"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.23"
msgid "Manāpameva bhāseyya,"
msgstr "One should say what is pleasant,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.24"
msgid "nāmanāpaṃ kudācanaṃ;"
msgstr "Never what is unpleasant."

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.25"
msgid "Manāpaṃ bhāsamānassa,"
msgstr "For him of pleasant speech,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.26"
msgid "garuṃ bhāraṃ udabbahi;"
msgstr "Heavy loads got carried,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.27"
msgid "Dhanañca naṃ alābhesi,"
msgstr "And he obtained wealth;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.28"
msgid "tena cattamano ahūti."
msgstr "And he was delighted with that."

#. </p></blockquote></div><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa33"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.29"
msgid "Tadāpi me, bhikkhave, amanāpā khuṃsanā vambhanā."
msgstr "Even at that time, monks, reviling and insulting was unpleasant to me."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.30"
msgid "Kimaṅgaṃ pana etarahi manāpā bhavissati khuṃsanā vambhanā?"
msgstr "How then could reviling and insulting be pleasant now?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.31"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.32"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.32a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa34"></a>
#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.33"
msgid "“Omasavāde pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk speaks abusively, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”"

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs1.2.34"
msgid "(<em>2</em>:<strong>51</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="pts-cs-empty" id="bu-pc.2.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.2.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa35"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.1"
msgid "Omasavādo nāma"
msgstr "Speaks abusively:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.2"
msgid "dasahi ākārehi omasati—"
msgstr "he abuses in ten ways:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.3"
msgid "jātiyāpi, nāmenapi, gottenapi, kammenapi, sippenapi, ābādhenapi, liṅgenapi, kilesenapi, āpattiyāpi, akkosenapi."
msgstr "about caste, about name, about family, about work, about craft, about illnesses, about physical traits, about defilements, about offenses, and by insulting."

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.3a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.3b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h4><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa36"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.4"
msgid "Jāti nāma"
msgstr "Caste:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.5"
msgid "dve jātiyo—"
msgstr "there are two kinds of castes:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.6"
msgid "hīnā ca jāti ukkaṭṭhā ca jāti."
msgstr "low castes and high castes."

#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.7"
msgid "Hīnā nāma"
msgstr "Low castes:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.174"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.8"
msgid "jāti—caṇḍālajāti, venajāti, nesādajāti, rathakārajāti, pukkusajāti."
msgstr "outcasts, bamboo workers, hunters, chariot-makers, waste-removers—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.9"
msgid "Esā hīnā nāma jāti."
msgstr "these are called “low castes.”"

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.10"
msgid "Ukkaṭṭhā nāma"
msgstr "High castes:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.11"
msgid "jāti—khattiyajāti, brāhmaṇajāti."
msgstr "aristocrats and brahmins—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.12"
msgid "Esā ukkaṭṭhā nāma jāti."
msgstr "these are called “high castes.”"

#. </span></span></p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa37"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.13"
msgid "Nāmaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Name:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.14"
msgid "dve nāmāni—"
msgstr "there are two kinds of names:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.15"
msgid "hīnañca nāmaṃ ukkaṭṭhañca nāmaṃ."
msgstr "low names and high names."

#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.16"
msgid "Hīnaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Low names:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.17"
msgid "nāmaṃ—avakaṇṇakaṃ, javakaṇṇakaṃ, dhaniṭṭhakaṃ, saviṭṭhakaṃ, kulavaḍḍhakaṃ, tesu tesu vā pana janapadesu oññātaṃ avaññātaṃ hīḷitaṃ paribhūtaṃ acittīkataṃ,"
msgstr "Avakaṇṇaka, Javakaṇṇaka, Dhaniṭṭhaka, Saviṭṭhaka, Kulavaḍḍhaka, or names, in whatever countries, that are despised, looked down upon, scorned, treated with contempt, disregarded—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.18"
msgid "etaṃ hīnaṃ nāma nāmaṃ."
msgstr "these are called “low names.”"

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.19"
msgid "Ukkaṭṭhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "High names:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.20"
msgid "nāmaṃ—buddhappaṭisaṃyuttaṃ, dhammappaṭisaṃyuttaṃ, saṃghappaṭisaṃyuttaṃ, tesu tesu vā pana janapadesu anoññātaṃ anavaññātaṃ ahīḷitaṃ aparibhūtaṃ cittīkataṃ,"
msgstr "those connected with the Buddha, connected with the Teaching, or connected with the Order, or names, in whatever countries, that are highly regarded, highly thought of, respected, valued, esteemed—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.21"
msgid "etaṃ ukkaṭṭhaṃ nāma nāmaṃ."
msgstr "these are called “high names.”"

#. </span></span></p><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa38"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.22"
msgid "Gottaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Family:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.23"
msgid "dve gottāni—"
msgstr "there are two kinds of families:"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.175"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.24"
msgid "hīnañca gottaṃ ukkaṭṭhañca gottaṃ."
msgstr "low families and high families."

#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.25"
msgid "Hīnaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Low families:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.26"
msgid "gottaṃ—kosiyagottaṃ, bhāradvājagottaṃ, tesu tesu vā pana janapadesu oññātaṃ avaññātaṃ hīḷitaṃ paribhūtaṃ acittīkataṃ,"
msgstr "the Kosiya family, the Bhāradvāja family, or families, in whatever countries, that are despised, looked down upon, scorned, treated with contempt, disregarded—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.27"
msgid "etaṃ hīnaṃ nāma gottaṃ."
msgstr "these are called “low families.”"

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.28"
msgid "Ukkaṭṭhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "High families:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.29"
msgid "gottaṃ—gotamagottaṃ, moggallānagottaṃ, kaccānagottaṃ, vāsiṭṭhagottaṃ, tesu tesu vā pana janapadesu anoññātaṃ anavaññātaṃ ahīḷitaṃ aparibhūtaṃ cittīkataṃ,"
msgstr "the Gotama family, the Moggallāna family, the Kaccāna family, the Vāsiṭṭha family, or families, in whatever countries, that are highly regarded, highly thought of, respected, valued, esteemed—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.30"
msgid "etaṃ ukkaṭṭhaṃ nāma gottaṃ."
msgstr "these are called “high families.”"

#. </span></span></p><p><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa39"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.31"
msgid "Kammaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Work:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.32"
msgid "dve kammāni—"
msgstr "there are two kinds of work:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.33"
msgid "hīnañca kammaṃ ukkaṭṭhañca kammaṃ."
msgstr "low work and high work."

#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.34"
msgid "Hīnaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Low work:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.35"
msgid "kammaṃ—koṭṭhakakammaṃ, pupphachaḍḍakakammaṃ, tesu tesu vā pana janapadesu oññātaṃ avaññātaṃ hīḷitaṃ paribhūtaṃ acittīkataṃ,"
msgstr "carpentry, waste-removing, or work, in whatever countries, that is despised, looked down upon, scorned, treated with contempt, disregarded—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.36"
msgid "etaṃ hīnaṃ nāma kammaṃ."
msgstr "this is called “low work.”"

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.37"
msgid "Ukkaṭṭhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "High work:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.38"
msgid "kammaṃ—kasi, vaṇijjā, gorakkhā, tesu tesu vā pana janapadesu anoññātaṃ anavaññātaṃ ahīḷitaṃ aparibhūtaṃ cittīkataṃ."
msgstr "farming, trade, cattle-keeping, or work, in whatever countries, that is highly regarded, highly thought of, respected, valued, esteemed—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.39"
msgid "Etaṃ ukkaṭṭhaṃ nāma kammaṃ."
msgstr "this is called “high work.”"

#. </span></span></p><p><a class="sc" id="12"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.7"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.176"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa40"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.40"
msgid "Sippaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Craft:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.41"
msgid "dve sippāni—"
msgstr "there are two kinds of crafts:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.42"
msgid "hīnañca sippaṃ ukkaṭṭhañca sippaṃ."
msgstr "low crafts and high crafts."

#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.43"
msgid "Hīnaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Low crafts:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.44"
msgid "sippaṃ—naḷakārasippaṃ, kumbhakārasippaṃ, pesakārasippaṃ, cammakārasippaṃ, nahāpitasippaṃ, tesu tesu vā pana janapadesu oññātaṃ avaññātaṃ hīḷitaṃ paribhūtaṃ acittīkataṃ."
msgstr "reed-work, pottery, weaving, leather-work, hairdressing, or crafts, in whatever countries, that are despised, looked down upon, scorned, treated with contempt, disregarded—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.45"
msgid "Etaṃ hīnaṃ nāma sippaṃ."
msgstr "these are called “low crafts.”"

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.46"
msgid "Ukkaṭṭhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "High crafts:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.177"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.47"
msgid "sippaṃ—muddā, gaṇanā, lekhā, tesu tesu vā pana janapadesu anoññātaṃ anavaññātaṃ ahīḷitaṃ aparibhūtaṃ cittīkataṃ,"
msgstr "calculating, accounting, writing, or crafts, in whatever countries, that are highly regarded, highly thought of, respected, valued, esteemed—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.48"
msgid "etaṃ ukkaṭṭhaṃ nāma sippaṃ."
msgstr "these are called “high crafts.”"

#. </span></span></p><p><a class="sc" id="13"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa41"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.49"
msgid "<span class=\"gloss\">Sabbepi <strong class=\"term\">ābādhā</strong> hīnā, api ca madhumeho ābādho ukkaṭṭho."
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Illnesses</strong>: <span class=\"gloss\">all are low, but there is the disease of diabetes which is high."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="14"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa42"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.50"
msgid "Liṅgaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Physical traits:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.51"
msgid "dve liṅgāni—"
msgstr "there are two kinds of physical traits:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.52"
msgid "hīnañca liṅgaṃ ukkaṭṭhañca liṅgaṃ."
msgstr "low physical traits and high physical traits."

#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.53"
msgid "Hīnaṃ nāma"
msgstr "Low physical traits:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.54"
msgid "liṅgaṃ—atidīghaṃ, atirassaṃ, atikaṇhaṃ, accodātaṃ,"
msgstr "too tall, too short, too dark, too fair—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.55"
msgid "etaṃ hīnaṃ nāma liṅgaṃ."
msgstr "these are called “low physical traits.”"

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.56"
msgid "Ukkaṭṭhaṃ nāma"
msgstr "High physical traits:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.57"
msgid "liṅgaṃ—nātidīghaṃ, nātirassaṃ, nātikaṇhaṃ, nāccodātaṃ."
msgstr "not too tall, not too short, not too dark, not too fair—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.58"
msgid "Etaṃ ukkaṭṭhaṃ nāma liṅgaṃ."
msgstr "these are called “high physical traits.”"

#. </span></span></p><p><a class="sc" id="15"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa43"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.59"
msgid "<span class=\"gloss\">Sabbepi <strong class=\"term\">kilesā</strong> hīnā."
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Defilements:</strong> <span class=\"gloss\">all are low."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="16"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa44"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.60"
msgid "<span class=\"gloss\">Sabbāpi <strong class=\"term\">āpattiyo</strong> hīnā."
msgstr "<strong class=\"term\">Offenses</strong>: <span class=\"gloss\">all are low,"

#. <span class="note" hidden>The English translation cannot properly capture the Pali, in which the word for “offense” and “attainment” is the same, <i lang="pli">āpatti</i>.</span> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.61"
msgid "Api ca sotāpattisamāpatti ukkaṭṭhā."
msgstr "but there is the attainment of stream-entry which is high."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="17"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa45"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.62"
msgid "Akkoso nāma"
msgstr "Insults:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.178"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.63"
msgid "dve akkosā—"
msgstr "there are two kinds of insults:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.64"
msgid "hīno ca akkoso ukkaṭṭho ca akkoso."
msgstr "low insults and high insults."

#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.65"
msgid "Hīno nāma"
msgstr "Low insults:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.66"
msgid "akkoso—oṭṭhosi, meṇḍosi, goṇosi, gadrabhosi, tiracchānagatosi, nerayikosi;"
msgstr "“you’re a camel/you’re a ram/you’re an ox/you’re a donkey/you’re an animal/you’re bound for hell;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.67"
msgid "natthi tuyhaṃ sugati, duggatiyeva tuyhaṃ pāṭikaṅkhāti, yakārena vā bhakārena vā, kāṭakoṭacikāya vā,"
msgstr "you’re not going to a good destination/you can only expect a bad destination,” or adding the disparaging endings <i lang=\"pli\">ya</i> or <i lang=\"pli\">bha</i> to someone’s name, or calling someone words for the male and female genitals—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.68"
msgid "eso hīno nāma akkoso."
msgstr "these are called “low insults.”"

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.69"
msgid "Ukkaṭṭho nāma"
msgstr "High insults:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.70"
msgid "akkoso—paṇḍitosi, byattosi, medhāvīsi, bahussutosi, dhammakathikosi,"
msgstr "“you’re wise/you’re competent/you’re intelligent/you’re learned/you’re an expounder of the Teaching;"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.71"
msgid "natthi tuyhaṃ duggati, sugatiyeva tuyhaṃ pāṭikaṅkhāti,"
msgstr "you’re not going to a bad destination/you can only expect a good destination”—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.1.72"
msgid "eso ukkaṭṭho nāma akkoso."
msgstr "these are called “high insults.”"

#. </span></span></p><h4>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Exposition"

#. </h4><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.0b"
msgid ""
msgstr "Abuse about caste"

#. </h5><p><a class="sc" id="18"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.2.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa46"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.1"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo hīnena hīnaṃ vadeti, caṇḍālaṃ venaṃ nesādaṃ rathakāraṃ pukkusaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is low to one who is low—an outcast/a bamboo worker/a hunter/a chariot-maker/a waste-remover—"

#. VAR: caṇḍālosi, venosi, nesādosi, rathakārosi, pukkusosī”ti bhaṇati → vadetīti uddeso. bhaṇatīti vitthāro (vajirabuddhi)
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.2"
msgid "“caṇḍālosi, venosi, nesādosi, rathakārosi, pukkusosī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re an outcast/you’re a bamboo worker/you’re a hunter/you’re a chariot-maker/you’re a waste-remover,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="19"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa47"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.3"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo hīnena ukkaṭṭhaṃ vadeti, khattiyaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is low to one who is high—an aristocrat/a brahmin—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.4"
msgid "“caṇḍālosi, venosi, nesādosi, rathakārosi, pukkusosī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re an outcast/you’re a bamboo worker/you’re a hunter/you’re a chariot-maker/you’re a waste-remover,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="20"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa48"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.5"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo ukkaṭṭhena hīnaṃ vadeti, caṇḍālaṃ venaṃ nesādaṃ rathakāraṃ pukkusaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is high to one who is low—an outcast/a bamboo worker/a hunter/a chariot-maker/a waste-remover—"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.179"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.6"
msgid "“khattiyosi, brāhmaṇosī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re an aristocrat/you’re a brahmin,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="21"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.8"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa49"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.7"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo ukkaṭṭhena ukkaṭṭhaṃ vadeti, khattiyaṃ brāhmaṇaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is high to one who is high—an aristocrat/a brahmin—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.8"
msgid "“khattiyosi, brāhmaṇosī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re an aristocrat/you’re a brahmin,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.8a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Abuse about name"

#. </h5><p><a class="sc" id="22"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa50"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.9"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo hīnena hīnaṃ vadeti, avakaṇṇakaṃ javakaṇṇakaṃ dhaniṭṭhakaṃ saviṭṭhakaṃ kulavaḍḍhakaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is low to one who is low—an Avakaṇṇaka/a Javakaṇṇaka/a Dhaniṭṭhaka/a Saviṭṭhaka/a Kulavaḍḍhaka—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.10"
msgid "“avakaṇṇakosi, javakaṇṇakosi, dhaniṭṭhakosi, saviṭṭhakosi, kulavaḍḍhakosī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re an Avakaṇṇaka/you’re a Javakaṇṇaka/you’re a Dhaniṭṭhaka/you’re a Saviṭṭhaka/you’re a Kulavaḍḍhaka,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="23"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa51"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.11"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo hīnena ukkaṭṭhaṃ vadeti, buddharakkhitaṃ dhammarakkhitaṃ saṃgharakkhitaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is low to one who is high—a Buddharakkhita/a Dhammarakkhita/a Sangharakkhita—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.12"
msgid "“avakaṇṇakosi, javakaṇṇakosi, dhaniṭṭhakosi, saviṭṭhakosi, kulavaḍḍhakosī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re an Avakaṇṇaka/you’re a Javakaṇṇaka/you’re a Dhaniṭṭhaka/you’re a Saviṭṭhaka/you’re a Kulavaḍḍhaka,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="24"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa52"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.13"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo ukkaṭṭhena hīnaṃ vadeti, avakaṇṇakaṃ javakaṇṇakaṃ dhaniṭṭhakaṃ saviṭṭhakaṃ kulavaḍḍhakaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is high to one who is low—an Avakaṇṇaka/a Javakaṇṇaka/a Dhaniṭṭhaka/a Saviṭṭhaka/a Kulavaḍḍhaka—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.14"
msgid "“buddharakkhitosi, dhammarakkhitosi, saṃgharakkhitosī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re a Buddharakkhita/you’re a Dhammarakkhita/you’re a Sangharakkhita,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="25"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa53"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.15"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo ukkaṭṭhena ukkaṭṭhaṃ vadeti, buddharakkhitaṃ dhammarakkhitaṃ saṃgharakkhitaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is high to one who is high—a Buddharakkhita/a Dhammarakkhita/a Sangharakkhita—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.16"
msgid "“buddharakkhitosi, dhammarakkhitosi, saṃgharakkhitosī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re a Buddharakkhita/you’re a Dhammarakkhita/you’re a Sangharakkhita,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.16a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Abuse about family"

#. </h5><p><a class="sc" id="26"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa54"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.17"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo hīnena hīnaṃ vadeti, kosiyaṃ bhāradvājaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is low to one who is low—one from the Kosiya family/one from the Bhāradvāja family—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.18"
msgid "“kosiyosi, bhāradvājosī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re a Kosiya/you’re a Bhāradvāja,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="27"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa55"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.19"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo hīnena ukkaṭṭhaṃ vadeti, gotamaṃ moggallānaṃ kaccānaṃ vāsiṭṭhaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is low to one who is high—one from the Gotama family/one from the Moggallāna family/one from the Kaccāna family/one from the Vāsiṭṭha family—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.20"
msgid "“kosiyosi, bhāradvājosī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re a Kosiya/you’re a Bhāradvāja,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="28"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa56"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.21"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo ukkaṭṭhena hīnaṃ vadeti, kosiyaṃ bhāradvājaṃ—"
