#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="51"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa79"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.67"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo hīnena ukkaṭṭhaṃ vadeti, sotāpannaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is low to one who is high—a stream-enterer—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.68"
msgid "“pārājikaṃ ajjhāpannosi … pe … dubbhāsitaṃ ajjhāpannosī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’ve committed an offense entailing expulsion/you’ve committed an offense entailing suspension/you’ve committed a serious offense/you’ve committed an offense entailing confession/you’ve committed an offense entailing acknowledgment/you’ve committed an offense of wrong conduct/you’ve committed an offense of bad speech,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="52"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa80"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.69"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo ukkaṭṭhena hīnaṃ vadeti, pārājikaṃ ajjhāpannaṃ … pe … dubbhāsitaṃ ajjhāpannaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is high to one who is low—one who has committed an offense entailing expulsion/one who has committed an offense entailing suspension/one who has committed a serious offense/one who has committed an offense entailing confession/one who has committed an offense entailing acknowledgment/one who has committed an offense of wrong conduct/one who has committed an offense of bad speech—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.70"
msgid "“sotāpannosī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re a stream-enterer,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="53"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa81"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.71"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo ukkaṭṭhena ukkaṭṭhaṃ vadeti, sotāpannaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is high to one who is high—a stream-enterer—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.72"
msgid "“sotāpannosī”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re a stream-enterer,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.72a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Insulting abuse"

#. </h5><p><a class="sc" id="54"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa82"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.73"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo hīnena hīnaṃ vadeti, oṭṭhaṃ meṇḍaṃ goṇaṃ gadrabhaṃ tiracchānagataṃ nerayikaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is low to one who is low—a camel/a ram/an ox/a donkey/an animal/one bound for hell—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.74"
msgid "“oṭṭhosi, meṇḍosi, goṇosi, gadrabhosi, tiracchānagatosi, nerayikosi, natthi tuyhaṃ sugati, duggati yeva tuyhaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re a camel/you’re a ram/you’re an ox/you’re a donkey/you’re an animal/you’re not going to a good destination/you can only expect a bad destination,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="55"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa83"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.75"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo hīnena ukkaṭṭhaṃ vadeti, paṇḍitaṃ byattaṃ medhāviṃ bahussutaṃ dhammakathikaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is low to one who is high—one who is wise/one who is competent/one who is intelligent/one who is learned/one who is an expounder of the Teaching—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.76"
msgid "“oṭṭhosi, meṇḍosi, goṇosi, gadrabhosi, tiracchānagatosi, nerayikosi, natthi tuyhaṃ sugati, duggatiyeva tuyhaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re a camel/you’re a ram/you’re an ox/you’re a donkey/you’re an animal/you’re not going to a good destination/you can only expect a bad destination,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="56"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa84"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.77"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo ukkaṭṭhena hīnaṃ vadeti, oṭṭhaṃ meṇḍaṃ goṇaṃ gadrabhaṃ tiracchānagataṃ nerayikaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is high to one who is low—a camel/a ram/an ox/a donkey/an animal/one bound for hell—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.78"
msgid "“paṇḍitosi, byattosi, medhāvīsi, bahussutosi, dhammakathikosi, natthi tuyhaṃ duggati, sugatiyeva tuyhaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re wise/you’re competent/you’re intelligent/you’re learned/you’re an expounder of the Teaching/you’re not going to a bad destination/you can only expect a good destination,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="57"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa85"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.182"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.79"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo ukkaṭṭhena ukkaṭṭhaṃ vadeti, paṇḍitaṃ byattaṃ medhāviṃ bahussutaṃ dhammakathikaṃ—"
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says what is high to one who is high—one who is wise/one who is competent/one who is intelligent/one who is learned/one who is an expounder of the Teaching—"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.2.80"
msgid "“paṇḍitosi, byattosi, medhāvīsi, bahussutosi, dhammakathikosi, natthi tuyhaṃ duggati, sugati yeva tuyhaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya pācittiyassa."
msgstr "saying, “You’re wise/you’re competent/you’re intelligent/you’re learned/you’re an expounder of the Teaching/you’re not going to a bad destination/you can only expect a good destination,” then for every statement, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. </p><h5>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.0a"
msgid ""
msgstr "Indirect abuse"

#. </h5><p><a class="sc" id="58"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.2.2.3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa86"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.1"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo evaṃ vadeti, “santi idhekacce caṇḍālā venā nesādā rathakārā pukkusā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says this, “There are outcasts/bamboo workers/hunters/chariot-makers/waste-removers, right here,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="59"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa87"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.2"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo evaṃ vadeti, “santi idhekacce khattiyā, brāhmaṇā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says this, “There are aristocrats/brahmins, right here,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="60"></a><a class="pts-vp-pli" id="pts-vp-pli4.10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa88"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.3"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo evaṃ vadeti, “santi idhekacce avakaṇṇakā javakaṇṇakā dhaniṭṭhakā saviṭṭhakā kulavaḍḍhakā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says this, “There are Avakaṇṇakas/Javakaṇṇakas/Dhaniṭṭhakas/Saviṭṭhakas/Kulavaḍḍhakas, right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.4"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce buddharakkhitā dhammarakkhitā saṃgharakkhitā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "“There are Buddharakkhitas/Dhammarakkhitas/Sangharakkhitas, right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.5"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce kosiyā bhāradvājā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "“There are Kosiyas/Bhāradvājas, right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.6"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce gotamā moggallānā kaccānā vāsiṭṭhā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "“There are Gotamas/Moggallānas/Kaccānas/Vāsiṭṭhas, right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.7"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce koṭṭhakā pupphachaḍḍakā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "“There are carpenters/waste-removers, right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.8"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce kassakā vāṇijā gorakkhā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "“There are farmers/traders/cattle-keepers, right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.9"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce naḷakārā kumbhakārā pesakārā cammakārā nahāpitā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "“There are reed-workers/potters/weavers/leather-workers/hairdressers, right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.10"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce muddikā gaṇakā lekhakā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "“There are calculators/accountants/scribes, right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.11"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce kuṭṭhikā gaṇḍikā kilāsikā sosikā apamārikā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "“There are lepers/ones with boils/ones with tuberculosis/epileptics, right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.12"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce madhumehikā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "“There are diabetics right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.13"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce atidīghā atirassā atikaṇhā accodātā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "“There are some who are too tall/some who are too short/some who are too dark/some who are too fair, right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.14"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce nātidīghā nātirassā nātikaṇhā nāccodātā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "“There are some who are not too tall/some who are not too short/some who are not too dark/some who are not too fair, right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.15"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce rāgapariyuṭṭhitā dosapariyuṭṭhitā mohapariyuṭṭhitā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "“There are some who are full of sensual desire/some who are full of ill-will/some who are full of confusion, right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.16"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce vītarāgā vītadosā vītamohā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "“There are some without sensual desire/some without ill-will/some without confusion, right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.17"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce pārājikaṃ ajjhāpannā … pe …."
msgstr "“There are some who have committed an offense entailing expulsion/ … /"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.18"
msgid "dubbhāsitaṃ ajjhāpannā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "some who have committed an offense of bad speech, right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.19"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce sotāpannā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "“There are stream-enterers right here” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.20"
msgid "“Santi idhekacce oṭṭhā meṇḍā goṇā gadrabhā tiracchānagatā nerayikā, natthi tesaṃ sugati, duggatiyeva tesaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "“There are camels/rams/oxen/donkeys/animals/those bound for hell/those who are not going to a good destination/those who can only expect a bad destination, right here,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="61"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa89"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.3.21"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo evaṃ vadeti, “santi idhekacce paṇḍitā byattā, medhāvī bahussutā dhammakathikā, natthi tesaṃ duggati, sugatiyeva tesaṃ pāṭikaṅkhā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says this, “There are wise ones/competent ones/intelligent ones/learned ones/expounders of the Teaching/those who are not going to a bad destination/those who can only expect a good destination, right here,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="62"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.2.2.4"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="BD.2.183"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa90"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.4.1"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo evaṃ vadeti, “ye nūna caṇḍālā venā nesādā rathakārā pukkusā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya dukkaṭassa … pe …."
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says this, “Perhaps these are outcasts/bamboo workers/hunters/chariot-makers/waste-removers,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct. …"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="63"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa91"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.4.2"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo evaṃ vadeti, “ye nūna paṇḍitā byattā medhāvī bahussutā dhammakathikā”ti bhaṇati, āpatti vācāya, vācāya dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says this, “Perhaps these are wise ones/competent ones/intelligent ones/learned ones/expounders of the Teaching,” then for every statement, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><hr><p><a class="sc" id="64"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-pc.2.2.5"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="wt-pa92"></a> 
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc2:pts-cs2.5.1"
msgid "Upasampanno upasampannaṃ khuṃsetukāmo vambhetukāmo maṅkukattukāmo evaṃ vadeti, “na mayaṃ caṇḍālā venā nesādā rathakārā pukkusā”ti bhaṇati … pe …."
msgstr "If one who is fully ordained, wishing to revile, wishing to insult, wishing to humiliate another who is fully ordained, says this, “We’re not outcasts/bamboo workers/hunters/chariot-makers/waste-removers” …"

